---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Cookie Policy"
  description="Cookie policy for Betting Maths, explaining essential cookies, Google Analytics cookies, consent choices, cookie settings and possible future advertising or affiliate cookies."
>
  <section class="content-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Cookie policy</p>
    <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      This Cookie Policy explains how Betting Maths uses cookies and similar technologies, including Google Analytics cookies.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Summary:</strong> Betting Maths uses essential site functionality and only loads Google Analytics after a visitor accepts analytics cookies. Visitors can reject non-essential cookies and can change their choice using the Cookie settings button.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>What are cookies?</h2>
    <p>
      Cookies are small files stored on a device by a website. They can help websites work properly, remember choices, measure site usage, support advertising or track referrals.
    </p>
    <p>
      Similar technologies may also store or access information on a device. This policy uses “cookies” as a simple term for cookies and similar technologies.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>How Betting Maths uses cookies</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths currently uses cookies or browser storage for two main purposes:
    </p>

    <table class="cookie-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Purpose</th>
          <th>Used for</th>
          <th>Essential?</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Cookie consent choice</td>
          <td>Remembering whether a visitor accepted or rejected analytics cookies.</td>
          <td>Yes, for remembering the user’s choice.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Google Analytics</td>
          <td>Understanding how visitors use the site so pages, calculators and guides can be improved.</td>
          <td>No. Analytics only loads after consent.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Cookie consent choice</h2>
    <p>
      When a visitor chooses to accept or reject analytics cookies, Betting Maths stores that choice in the browser so the banner does not appear on every page.
    </p>
    <p>
      This choice is stored using browser local storage under the name:
    </p>

    <div class="code-box">
      bettingMathsCookieConsent
    </div>

    <p>
      This stores whether analytics cookies were accepted or rejected. It is not used to identify a person.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Google Analytics cookies</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths uses Google Analytics to understand how people use the site. This helps show which calculators and guides are useful, which pages need improvement, and whether the site is working properly.
    </p>
    <p>
      Google Analytics may use cookies to collect information such as page views, approximate location, device type, browser type and general interaction data.
    </p>

    <table class="cookie-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Cookie</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
          <th>Typical duration</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>_ga</td>
          <td>Used by Google Analytics to distinguish visitors.</td>
          <td>Up to 2 years, depending on Google settings and browser behaviour.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>_ga_*</td>
          <td>Used by Google Analytics 4 to help maintain session and measurement information.</td>
          <td>May vary depending on Google settings and browser behaviour.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Important:</strong> Google Analytics is not loaded by Betting Maths unless the visitor clicks “Accept analytics” on the cookie banner.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Accepting or rejecting analytics cookies</h2>
    <p>
      When the cookie banner appears, visitors can choose:
    </p>

    <ul class="standard-list">
      <li><strong>Accept analytics</strong> — Google Analytics loads and may set analytics cookies.</li>
      <li><strong>Reject non-essential</strong> — Google Analytics does not load, and analytics cookies are cleared where possible.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      A small Cookie settings button remains available so visitors can reopen the banner and change their choice.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>How to change your cookie choice</h2>
    <p>
      Use the Cookie settings button in the bottom corner of the site to reopen the cookie banner.
    </p>
    <p>
      Visitors can also clear cookies and site data in their browser settings. Clearing browser data may reset the cookie banner choice.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Future advertising or affiliate cookies</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths may include advertising, affiliate links or sponsored placements in the future.
    </p>
    <p>
      If that happens, this Cookie Policy and the Privacy Policy should be updated to explain what additional cookies or tracking technologies are used, why they are used, and what choices visitors have.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Third-party websites</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths may link to external websites, including responsible gambling resources, official support organisations, search engines, analytics providers or other informational pages.
    </p>
    <p>
      External websites may use their own cookies and privacy practices. Betting Maths does not control cookies set by third-party websites once a visitor leaves this site.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>More privacy information</h2>
    <p>
      For more information about privacy, analytics, data sharing and future advertising or affiliate wording, read the Privacy Policy.
    </p>

    <div class="button-row">
      <a class="button primary" href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>
      <a class="button secondary" href="/responsible-gambling/">Responsible Gambling</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Changes to this Cookie Policy</h2>
    <p>
      This Cookie Policy may be updated as Betting Maths develops, especially if new analytics tools, advertising, affiliate links or cookie features are added.
    </p>
    <p>
      Last updated: 3 May 2026.
    </p>
  </section>

  <style>
    .article-section {
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }

    .standard-list {
      padding-left: 1.3rem;
    }

    .standard-list li {
      margin: 0.45rem 0;
    }

    .cookie-table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      background: white;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 14px;
      overflow: hidden;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }

    .cookie-table th,
    .cookie-table td {
      padding: 0.75rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      text-align: left;
      vertical-align: middle;
    }

    .cookie-table th {
      color: var(--color-navy);
      background: #f4f7fa;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .cookie-table tr:last-child td {
      border-bottom: 0;
    }

    .code-box {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 0.65rem 0.85rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: var(--color-bg);
      color: var(--color-navy);
      font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Liberation Mono", "Courier New", monospace;
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .article-section a {
      color: var(--color-green-dark);
      font-weight: 800;
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
    }
  </style>
</MainLayout>
